OK, I decided to see what all the fuss was about after the news announcements, so I installed the Service NSW app from Google Play. The newest reviews are pretty scathing, but I persisted. It installed. I ran it. It asked me to sign into my ServiceNSW account. I had to look that up because I hadn't needed to deal with it since paying my rego in April. It asked me to set a four digit pin and whether I wanted to use my fingerprint to unlock the app. YOU ARE NOT TAKING MY CHILD'S FINGERPRINT! So I said yes. I got in and the first thing that appeared was "Get my Digital Driver's Licence". A few seconds later, I had it! I also had a link to instantly see all my traffic fines and demerits (none for both of course) as well as my car rego details. And I got to see my digital licence.
